{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881969800,"sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad046340018B2PVHvSJe3PLw","messageID":"msg_d7ad02e3a001BYjc4wPdotpHrq","sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** pkg/picod  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: \n10: Provide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Valid token allows request\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token in the Authorization header\n22: - **WHEN** a request is made to a PicoD execution endpoint\n23: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL validate the token and allow the request to proceed\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Missing token returns 401\n26: - **GIVEN** a request without an Authorization header\n27: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n28: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Invalid token format returns 401\n31: - **GIVEN** a request with an Authorization header not starting with \"Bearer \"\n32: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n33: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid authorization format\"}`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n36: - **GIVEN** a request with an expired JWT token\n37: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Malformed token returns 401\n41: - **GIVEN** a request with a malformed JWT token\n42: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token malformed\"}`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n46: - **GIVEN** a request with a JWT token signed with wrong key\n47: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token signature invalid\"}`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Token Claims Extraction and Context Propagation\n53: \n54: The system SHALL extract JWT claims and store them in the request context for downstream handlers.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Claims stored in context\n57: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id claim\n58: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n59: - **THEN** the extracted claims SHALL be stored in the request context\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Session ID extracted from token\n62: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n63: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n64: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve session_id from context\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: User ID extracted from token\n67: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with user_id=\"user-456\"\n68: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n69: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve user_id from context\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Sandbox ID extracted from token\n72: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with sandbox_id=\"sandbox-789\"\n73: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n74: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve sandbox_id from context\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Namespace extracted from token\n77: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with namespace=\"default\"\n78: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n79: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve namespace from context\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Multiple claims extracted\n82: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id, user_id, sandbox_id, namespace, and runtime_kind claims\n83: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n84: - **THEN** all claims SHALL be available in the context for downstream use\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Session ID Validation Middleware\n89: \n90: The system SHALL verify that the session_id claim is present and valid.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing session_id returns 403\n93: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token without a session_id claim\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id claim is required\"}`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Empty session_id returns 403\n98: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with empty session_id=\"\"\n99: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n100: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id cannot be empty\"}`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Session ID matches request parameter\n103: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/abc123\n104: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n105: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Session ID mismatch returns 403\n108: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/def456\n109: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n110: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session access denied\"}`\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: Optional Authentication Support\n115: \n116: The system SHALL support optional authentication for specific endpoints.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Optional auth allows anonymous requests\n119: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n120: - **WHEN** a request without a token is made\n121: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed without claims in context\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Optional auth extracts claims when present\n124: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n125: - **WHEN** a request with a valid token is made\n126: - **THEN** the claims SHALL be extracted and stored in context\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Optional auth ignores invalid tokens\n129: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n130: - **WHEN** a request with an invalid token is made\n131: - **THEN** the request SHALL proceed without claims (invalid token is treated as no token)\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: JWT Configuration\n136: \n137: The system SHALL support configurable JWT settings for the PicoD middleware.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Configuration from environment variables\n140: - **GIVEN** environment variables `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER`, `PICOD_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`, and `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY`\n141: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is initialized\n142: - **THEN** the configuration SHALL be populated from these environment variables\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Configuration with public key PEM\n145: - **GIVEN** a valid RSA public key in PEM format in configuration\n146: - **WHEN** the middleware validates tokens\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL use the configured public key to verify signatures\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Configuration with JWKS endpoint\n150: - **GIVEN** a JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) endpoint URL in configuration\n151: - **WHEN** the middleware needs to validate tokens\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL fetch the public key from the JWKS endpoint\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Invalid configuration returns error\n155: - **GIVEN** an invalid JWT configuration (e.g., empty issuer)\n156: - **WHEN** the middleware is initialized\n157: - **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n160: - **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n161: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is loaded\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL use sensible defaults (issuer=\"picod\", expiry=5m)\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Token Refresh Support\n167: \n168: The system SHALL support token refresh for extended sessions.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Refresh token endpoint\n171: - **GIVEN** a valid refresh token\n172: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/auth/refresh` with the refresh token\n173: - **THEN** the server SHALL return a new access token and refresh token pair\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Expired refresh token returns 401\n176: - **GIVEN** an expired refresh token\n177: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n178: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"refresh token expired\"}`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Invalid refresh token returns 401\n181: - **GIVEN** an invalid refresh token\n182: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n183: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid refresh token\"}`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Public Key Endpoint\n188: \n189: The system SHALL expose a public key endpoint for token verification by clients.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Get public key\n192: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with RSA keys\n193: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/.well-known/jwks.json`\n194: - **THEN** the server SHALL return the public key in JWKS format\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Public key includes key ID\n197: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with key versioning\n198: - **WHEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n199: - **THEN** the response SHALL include the key ID (kid) for each key\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Public key algorithm specified\n202: - **GIVEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n203: - **WHEN** the response is returned\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL include the algorithm (alg: RS256) and key type (kty: RSA)\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n209: \n210: The system SHALL expose metrics for JWT middleware operations.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Token validation counter\n213: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n214: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validations_total` counter with labels for result (success/failure)\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Token validation latency\n218: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n219: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n220: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validation_duration_seconds` histogram\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Active session tracking\n223: - **GIVEN** tokens are being validated\n224: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_active_sessions` gauge with session_id labels\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Logging\n230: \n231: The system SHALL implement structured logging for JWT middleware operations.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Successful authentication logged\n234: - **GIVEN** a request with valid token is processed\n235: - **WHEN** authentication succeeds\n236: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, user_id, endpoint, duration\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Failed authentication logged\n239: - **GIVEN** a request with invalid token is processed\n240: - **WHEN** authentication fails\n241: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: error, error_code, endpoint, remote_addr\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Token refresh logged\n244: - **GIVEN** a token refresh request is processed\n245: - **WHEN** refresh succeeds or fails\n246: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, result, duration\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n251: \n252: The system SHALL provide consistent error responses for authentication failures.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: WWW-Authenticate header on 401\n255: - **GIVEN** an unauthenticated request\n256: - **WHEN** the middleware returns HTTP 401\n257: - **THEN** the response SHALL include `WWW-Authenticate: Bearer` header\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JSON error response format\n260: - **GIVEN** an authentication error occurs\n261: - **WHEN** the error response is sent\n262: - **THEN** it SHALL be JSON with fields: error, message, code (optional)\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Error code classification\n265: - **GIVEN** various authentication failures\n266: - **WHEN** errors are returned\n267: - **THEN** each SHALL have a machine-readable code: TOKEN_EXPIRED, TOKEN_INVALID, TOKEN_MALFORMED, MISSING_CLAIMS\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## File Index\n272: \n273: | Path | Purpose |\n274: |------|---------|\n275: | `pkg/picod/jwt_middleware.go` | JWT authentication middleware implementation |\n276: | `pkg/picod/jwt_config.go` | JWT configuration structures and loading |\n277: | `pkg/picod/jwt_types.go` | JWT types and context keys for PicoD |\n278: | `pkg/picod/jwt_handlers.go` | HTTP handlers for auth endpoints (refresh, JWKS) |\n279: | `pkg/picod/errors.go` | JWT and authentication error definitions |\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## Dependencies\n284: \n285: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n286: |------------|---------|---------|\n287: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token parsing and validation |\n288: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Local | Shared JWT types and utilities |\n289: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n290: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics collection |\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## API Endpoints\n295: \n296: | Method | Path | Auth Required | Description |\n297: |--------|------|---------------|-------------|\n298: | POST | `/execute/{session_id}` | Yes | Execute command in sandbox |\n299: | GET | `/execute/{id}/status` | Yes | Get execution status |\n300: | GET | `/execute/{id}/output` | Yes | Stream execution output |\n301: | DELETE | `/execute/{id}` | Yes | Cancel execution |\n302: | POST | `/auth/refresh` | No | Refresh access token |\n303: | GET | `/.well-known/jwks.json` | No | Get public keys in JWKS format |\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Integration Points\n308: \n309: | Component | Integration |\n310: |-----------|-------------|\n311: | `pkg/router` | Reuses JWTManager for token validation; imports TokenClaims type |\n312: | `pkg/picod/executor.go` | Reads session_id from context to validate execution requests |\n313: | `pkg/store` | May store refresh token metadata for revocation |\n314: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Coordinates JWT configuration across components |\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Notes\n319: \n320: - The PicoD JWT middleware leverages the existing `pkg/router` JWT implementation where possible\n321: - Token claims must include `session_id` for all PicoD execution endpoints\n322: - The middleware supports both mandatory and optional authentication patterns\n323: - Public keys are exposed via JWKS endpoint for external verification\n324: - Metrics are prefixed with `picod_` to distinguish from router metrics\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nProvide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid token allows request","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881969743,"end":1775881969798}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881969802,"sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad03e2e001SYY1Y36SE60C4V","messageID":"msg_d7ad02e3a001BYjc4wPdotpHrq","sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n2: \n3: ## AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/agentd` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | S (Small) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the Agentd idle cleanup controller that automatically deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when they have been inactive beyond a configured timeout. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **Reconciler Controller**: A controller-runtime reconciler that watches `Sandbox` resources and manages their lifecycle based on activity timestamps\n19: 2. **Idle Detection**: Reading and parsing the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine when a sandbox was last active\n20: 3. **Automatic Cleanup**: Deleting sandboxes that have exceeded the `SessionExpirationTimeout` (15 minutes)\n21: 4. **Efficient Requeueing**: Scheduling reconciliation at the exact expiration time to minimize unnecessary API calls\n22: 5. **Error Handling**: Graceful handling of parse errors, not-found errors, and deletion failures\n23: 6. **Binary Integration**: A standalone `agentd` binary that runs the controller using controller-runtime manager\n24: \n25: This controller integrates with the agentcube platform to ensure sandboxes don't consume resources indefinitely when idle, complementing the workload manager's sandbox creation and session management capabilities.\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Scope\n30: \n31: ### In Scope\n32: \n33: | Item | Detail |\n34: |------|--------|\n35: | **Reconciler** | controller-runtime `Reconciler` implementation for Sandbox resources |\n36: | **Idle Detection** | Reading `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata |\n37: | **Time Parsing** | RFC3339 timestamp parsing with error handling |\n38: | **Expiration Logic** | Computing expiration time based on `SessionExpirationTimeout` |\n39: | **Resource Deletion** | Deleting Sandbox resources via Kubernetes client |\n40: | **Requeue Scheduling** | Smart requeue at expiration time for pending cleanups |\n41: | **Error Handling** | Proper handling of NotFound, parse errors, and delete errors |\n42: | **Manager Setup** | Controller-runtime manager configuration and startup |\n43: | **Scheme Registration** | Registration of Sandbox CRD types |\n44: | **Binary Entrypoint** | `cmd/agentd/main.go` with signal-driven shutdown |\n45: \n46: ### Out of Scope\n47: \n48: - Activity tracking/timestamp updates (handled by workload manager)\n49: - Custom idle timeout per sandbox (uses fixed 15-minute threshold)\n50: - Graceful shutdown of sandbox workloads before deletion\n51: - Cleanup of related Kubernetes resources (pods, secrets) - handled by ownerReferences\n52: - Metrics and monitoring endpoints\n53: - Leader election for multi-replica deployments\n54: - Webhook validation for Sandbox resources\n55: - Horizontal scaling considerations\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Design\n60: \n61: ### File Structure\n62: \n63: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n64: |------|------|--------------|\n65: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation | ~100 |\n66: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | Unit tests for reconciler | ~150 |\n67: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Binary entrypoint | ~60 |\n68: \n69: ### Architecture\n70: \n71: ```\n72: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n73: │                    Kubernetes Cluster                    │\n74: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n75: │  │              Agentd Controller                   │    │\n76: │  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n77: │  │  │         Controller-Runtime Manager         │  │    │\n78: │  │  │  ┌─────────┐  ┌─────────┐  ┌───────────┐  │  │    │\n79: │  │  │  │  Watch  │──►│Reconcile│──►│  Delete   │  │  │    │\n80: │  │  │  │ Sandbox │  │         │  │  Sandbox  │  │  │    │\n81: │  │  │  └─────────┘  └────┬────┘  └───────────┘  │  │    │\n82: │  │  │                    │                      │  │    │\n83: │  │  │              ┌─────┴─────┐                │  │    │\n84: │  │  │              ▼           ▼                │  │    │\n85: │  │  │        ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐         │  │    │\n86: │  │  │        │Parse Time│  │Schedule  │         │  │    │\n87: │  │  │        │RFC3339   │  │Requeue   │         │  │    │\n88: │  │  │        └──────────┘  └──────────┘         │  │    │\n89: │  │  └───────────────────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n90: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n91: │                           │                              │\n92: │                           ▼                              │\n93: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n94: │  │            Sandbox CRD (agents.x-k8s.io)         │    │\n95: │  │  metadata:                                       │    │\n96: │  │    annotations:                                  │    │\n97: │  │      last-activity-time: \"2026-03-21T10:00:00Z\" │    │\n98: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n99: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### Reconciliation Flow\n103: \n104: ```\n105: Reconcile(request)\n106:         │\n107:         ▼\n108: ┌──────────────┐\n109: │ Get Sandbox  │\n110: └──────────────┘\n111:         │\n112:         ├─ NotFound ──► Return (empty, nil)\n113:         │\n114:         ▼\n115: ┌──────────────────────────┐\n116: │ Read last-activity-time  │\n117: │ annotation               │\n118: └──────────────────────────┘\n119:         │\n120:         ├─ Missing/Empty ──► Return (empty, nil)\n121:         │\n122:         ▼\n123: ┌──────────────┐\n124: │ Parse Time   │\n125: │ (RFC3339)    │\n126: └──────────────┘\n127:         │\n128:         ├─ Parse Error ──► Return (RequeueAfter: 30s, err)\n129:         │\n130:         ▼\n131: ┌─────────────────────────┐\n132: │ Compute Expiration:     │\n133: │ lastActivity + 15min    │\n134: └─────────────────────────┘\n135:         │\n136:         ▼\n137:    Expired?\n138:         │\n139:    ┌────┴────┐\n140:    ▼         ▼\n141:   Yes       No\n142:    │         │\n143:    ▼         ▼\n144: ┌──────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n145: │Delete│  │Return RequeueAfter│\n146: │      │  │time.Until(expire) │\n147: └──┬───┘  └──────────────────┘\n148:    │\n149:    ▼\n150: ┌─────────────┐\n151: │ NotFound?   │\n152: └──────┬──────┘\n153:        │\n154:   ┌────┴────┐\n155:   ▼         ▼\n156:  Yes        No\n157:   │          │\n158:   ▼          ▼\n159: ┌──────┐  ┌─────────┐\n160: │Return│  │Return   │\n161: │ok    │  │error    │\n162: └──────┘  └─────────┘\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ### Core Types\n166: \n167: #### Reconciler Struct\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: type Reconciler struct {\n171:     client.Client\n172:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n173: }\n174: ```\n175: \n176: #### Key Constants\n177: \n178: ```go\n179: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n180: ```\n181: \n182: #### Reconcile Method Signature\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n186: ```\n187: \n188: #### SetupWithManager\n189: \n190: ```go\n191: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n192:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n193:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n194:         Complete(r)\n195: }\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## Execution Flows\n201: \n202: ### Successful Idle Cleanup\n203: \n204: ```\n205: Reconcile(ctx, req)\n206:     │\n207:     ▼\n208: sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}\n209: Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)\n210:     │\n211:     ▼\n212: lastActivityStr := sandbox.Annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n213:     │\n214:     ▼\n215: lastActivity, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n216:     │\n217:     ▼\n218: expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)\n219:     │\n220:     ▼\n221: time.Now().After(expirationTime) == true\n222:     │\n223:     ▼\n224: r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)\n225:     │\n226:     ▼\n227: Return ctrl.Result{}, nil\n228: ```\n229: \n230: ### Future Expiration (Requeue)\n231: \n232: ```\n233: Reconcile(ctx, req)\n234:     │\n235:     ▼\n236: sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}\n237: Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)\n238:     │\n239:     ▼\n240: lastActivityStr := sandbox.Annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n241:     │\n242:     ▼\n243: lastActivity, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n244:     │\n245:     ▼\n246: expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)\n247:     │\n248:     ▼\n249: time.Now().After(expirationTime) == false\n250:     │\n251:     ▼\n252: Return ctrl.Result{\n253:     RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime),\n254: }, nil\n255: ```\n256: \n257: ### Parse Error Recovery\n258: \n259: ```\n260: Reconcile(ctx, req)\n261:     │\n262:     ▼\n263: lastActivityStr := sandbox.Annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n264:     │\n265:     ▼\n266: lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n267:     │\n268:     ▼\n269: err != nil (malformed timestamp)\n270:     │\n271:     ▼\n272: Return ctrl.Result{\n273:     RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second,\n274: }, err\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### Binary Startup Flow\n278: \n279: ```\n280: main()\n281:     │\n282:     ▼\n283: schemeBuilder := runtime.NewScheme()\n284:     │\n285:     ▼\n286: scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder)\n287: sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder)\n288:     │\n289:     ▼\n290: mgr, _ := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n291:     Scheme: schemeBuilder,\n292:     Metrics: metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n293:     HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\",\n294: })\n295:     │\n296:     ▼\n297: ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n298:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n299:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n300:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n301:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n302:     })\n303:     │\n304:     ▼\n305: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n306: ```\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Error Handling\n311: \n312: ### Error Types\n313: \n314: | Error | Description |\n315: |-------|-------------|\n316: | `NotFound` | Sandbox already deleted or never existed |\n317: | `ParseError` | Invalid RFC3339 timestamp in annotation |\n318: | `DeleteError` | Kubernetes API delete operation failed |\n319: \n320: ### HTTP Responses\n321: \n322: | Scenario | Result | Error |\n323: |----------|--------|-------|\n324: | Sandbox not found | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n325: | No activity annotation | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n326: | Invalid timestamp | `RequeueAfter: 30s` | parse error |\n327: | Not yet expired | `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expiration)` | `nil` |\n328: | Delete succeeded | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n329: | Delete NotFound | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n330: | Delete other error | `ctrl.Result{}` | delete error |\n331: \n332: ---\n333: \n334: ## Security Considerations\n335: \n336: ### RBAC Requirements\n337: \n338: The `agentd` controller requires the following RBAC permissions:\n339: \n340: | Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n341: |----------|-------|--------|\n342: | `sandboxes` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` | Core reconciler operations |\n343: | `sandboxes/status` | `get`, `update` | Future status updates |\n344: \n345: ### Annotation Trust\n346: \n347: - The `last-activity-time` annotation is set by the workload manager, which is trusted\n348: - The reconciler only reads this annotation; it does not modify it\n349: - No validation of annotation origin is performed (relies on Kubernetes RBAC)\n350: \n351: ### Resource Cleanup\n352: \n353: - Deletion of Sandbox triggers cascade deletion of owned resources via ownerReferences\n354: - No direct deletion of Pods, Secrets, or other child resources\n355: - Follows standard Kubernetes garbage collection patterns\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## Impact Analysis\n360: \n361: ### Files Created\n362: \n363: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n364: |------|--------------|-------------|\n365: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | ~100 | Reconciler implementation |\n366: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | ~150 | Unit tests for reconciler |\n367: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | ~60 | Binary entrypoint |\n368: \n369: ### Dependencies\n370: \n371: ```go\n372: import (\n373:     \"context\"\n374:     \"time\"\n375:     \n376:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n377:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n378:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime\"\n379:     \"sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1\"\n380:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n381:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n382:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/metrics/server\"\n383:     \n384:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n385: )\n386: ```\n387: \n388: | Package | Purpose |\n389: |---------|---------|\n390: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Kubernetes controller framework |\n391: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Sandbox CRD types |\n392: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n393: \n394: ### Downstream Consumers\n395: \n396: | Consumer | Usage |\n397: |----------|-------|\n398: | Workload Manager | Sets `last-activity-time` annotation on sandboxes |\n399: | Sandbox CRD | Resource being reconciled and deleted |\n400: | Kubernetes GC | Cleans up owned resources after Sandbox deletion |\n401: \n402: ### Performance Characteristics\n403: \n404: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n405: |-----------|------------|-------|\n406: | Get Sandbox | O(1) | Single API call by name |\n407: | Delete Sandbox | O(1) | Single API call |\n408: | Requeue scheduling | O(1) | Computed from timestamp |\n409: | Memory usage | O(1) | Per-reconciler constant |\n410: \n411: ### Watched Resources\n412: \n413: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n414: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n415: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Creates, updates, deletes |\n416: \n417: ---\n418: \n419: ## Alternatives Considered\n420: \n421: ### Alternative 1: CronJob-based Cleanup\n422: \n423: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n424: |--------|------------|\n425: | **Pros** | Simpler implementation; no long-running process; uses existing Kubernetes primitives |\n426: | **Cons** | Polling overhead (fixed intervals); delayed cleanup (worst-case interval delay); requires cluster-wide list permissions |\n427: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Event-driven reconciler provides immediate response to sandbox changes and precise expiration scheduling |\n428: \n429: ### Alternative 2: OwnerReference with TTL\n430: \n431: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n432: |--------|------------|\n433: | **Pros** | Native Kubernetes feature; no custom controller needed; automatic garbage collection |\n434: | **Cons** | TTL is from creation time, not last activity; doesn't support idle-based cleanup; requires newer Kubernetes versions |\n435: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — TTL doesn't match idle-cleanup semantics; we need activity-based, not creation-based expiration |\n436: \n437: ### Alternative 3: Webhook-based Pre-Delete Validation\n438: \n439: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n440: |--------|------------|\n441: | **Pros** | Can block deletion if activity recent; validates before allowing delete |\n442: | **Cons** | More complex; requires webhook server; doesn't handle automatic cleanup |\n443: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Adds unnecessary complexity; reconciler pattern is standard for this use case |\n444: \n445: ### Alternative 4: Workload Manager Handles Cleanup\n446: \n447: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n448: |--------|------------|\n449: | **Pros** | Single component manages full lifecycle; no separate binary |\n450: | **Cons** | Violates separation of concerns; workload manager focuses on creation, not long-term maintenance; harder to scale independently |\n451: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Dedicated controller follows Kubernetes best practices for resource lifecycle management |\n452: \n453: ---\n454: \n455: ## Risks and Mitigations\n456: \n457: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n458: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n459: | Clock skew between controller and workload manager | Low | Medium | Both use Kubernetes API server time; RFC3339 includes timezone |\n460: | Requeue storm on many expiring sandboxes | Low | Medium | Natural spread from different creation times; controller-runtime rate limiting |\n461: | Sandbox deleted while active | Low | High | 15-minute grace period provides buffer; activity updates are frequent |\n462: | Parse errors from malformed timestamps | Low | Low | Requeue with 30s delay; eventually consistent |\n463: | API server unavailable | Low | High | Controller-runtime exponential backoff; eventual reconciliation |\n464: | Race condition between activity update and cleanup | Low | Medium | Requeue if not yet expired; next activity update will be seen |\n465: | Missing RBAC permissions | Medium | High | Clear error on startup; fail-fast in main.go |\n466: \n467: ---\n468: \n469: ## Verification\n470: \n471: ### Unit Tests\n472: \n473: ```bash\n474: # Run all agentd tests\n475: make test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n476: \n477: # Run with race detector\n478: go test -race ./pkg/agentd/...\n479: \n480: # Run specific test categories\n481: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestReconcile\"\n482: ```\n483: \n484: ### Integration Tests\n485: \n486: ```bash\n487: # Run integration tests\n488: make integration-test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n489: \n490: # With coverage\n491: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n492: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n493: ```\n494: \n495: ### Manual Verification\n496: \n497: ```bash\n498: # Build verification\n499: go build ./cmd/agentd/...\n500: \n501: # Run locally (requires kubeconfig)\n502: ./agentd\n503: \n504: # Lint check\n505: make lint PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n506: ```\n507: \n508: ### Test Scenarios\n509: \n510: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n511: |----------|-----------------|\n512: | Sandbox without annotation | No deletion, empty result |\n513: | Sandbox with valid recent timestamp | Requeue after time.Until(expiration) |\n514: | Sandbox expired (15+ min idle) | Delete called, success |\n515: | Sandbox already deleted | No error, empty result |\n516: | Invalid timestamp format | Requeue after 30s, error returned |\n517: | Delete returns NotFound | No error, empty result |\n518: | Delete returns other error | Error returned |\n519: | Parse timestamp at exact boundary | Correct expiration computation |\n520: | Concurrent sandbox updates | Handled by controller-runtime optimistic locking |\n521: \n522: ---\n523: \n524: ## References\n525: \n526: - [Idle Cleanup Design](idle-cleanup/design.md) — Detailed design document\n527: - [Idle Cleanup Spec](idle-cleanup/spec.md) — Specification with scenarios\n528: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n529: - [project.md](project.md) — Project context and architecture\n530: \n531: ---\n532: \n533: ## Success Criteria\n534: \n535: 1. ✅ Reconciler implementation correctly watches Sandbox resources\n536: 2. ✅ Last activity annotation is read and parsed from Sandbox metadata\n537: 3. ✅ Expiration is computed as lastActivity + 15 minutes\n538: 4. ✅ Expired sandboxes are deleted automatically\n539: 5. ✅ Non-expired sandboxes trigger requeue at expiration time\n540: 6. ✅ Parse errors trigger requeue with 30s delay\n541: 7. ✅ NotFound errors are handled gracefully\n542: 8. ✅ Binary starts successfully with controller-runtime manager\n543: 9. ✅ Scheme registration includes Sandbox CRD types\n544: 10. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n545: 11. ✅ Integration tests passing\n546: 12. ✅ Signal-driven shutdown works correctly\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: *AR-018 — Module: pkg/agentd — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 550 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/agentd` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Agentd idle cleanup controller that automatically deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when they have been inactive beyond a configured timeout. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Reconciler Controller**: A controller-runtime reconciler that watches `Sandbox` resources and manages their lifecycle based on activity timestamps\n2. **Idle Detection**: Reading and parsing the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine when a sandbox was last active\n3. **Automatic Cleanup**: Deleting sandboxes that have exceeded the `SessionExpirationTimeout` (15 minutes)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775881969738,"end":1775881969800}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881969806,"sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad059a9001ifePRhNlJEChp7","messageID":"msg_d7ad02e3a001BYjc4wPdotpHrq","sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775881969770,"end":1775881969803}}}}
