{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882114147,"sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad0e339001d0BSKjb27FLk9Y","messageID":"msg_d7ad0d054001vh6Tp5fPZOGead","sessionID":"ses_2853012c3ffeCKRazIanJjdzkh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **agentd** — Idle cleanup controller binary that runs the Sandbox reconciler\n2. **router** — HTTP session routing proxy with Gin framework\n3. **workload-manager** — Sandbox orchestration controller with Kubernetes CRD management\n4. **picod** — Sandbox daemon for code execution inside sandbox pods\n\nThese binaries serve as the deployment targets for the AgentCube platform, enabling independent scaling, deployment, and lifecycle management of each component.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Binary Entry Points** | 4 `main.go` files under `cmd/`: `agentd`, `router`, `workload-manager`, `picod` |\n| **Flag Parsing** | Standard Go `flag` package with `--help` support |\n| **Configuration** | CLI flags for service-specific settings (ports, timeouts, Kubernetes config) |\n| **Graceful Shutdown** | SIGINT/SIGTERM handling with configurable timeout |\n| **Dependency Wiring** | Initialize clients (Redis, Kubernetes, HTTP) from configuration |\n| **Service Startup** | Start controllers, HTTP servers, and reconcilers |\n| **Health Checks** | Basic liveness/readiness endpoints where applicable |\n| **Logging** | Structured startup logging with version and configuration |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Configuration file support (YAML/JSON config files)\n- Hot configuration reloading\n- Service discovery integration (Consul, etcd)\n- Metrics and monitoring endpoints (Prometheus)\n- Distributed tracing (Jaeger, Zipkin)\n- Circuit breaker patterns\n- Multi-instance leader election\n- Automated TLS certificate management\n- Plugin system for extensibility\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Idle cleanup controller binary | ~80 |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | Session routing proxy binary | ~100 |\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Sandbox orchestration binary | ~120 |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Sandbox daemon binary | ~90 |\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        AgentCube Platform                            │\n│                                                                      │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n│  │   agentd     │  │    router    │  │workload-mgr  │  │  picod   │ │\n│  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │ ┌──────┐ │ │\n│  │  │Reconciler│  │  │  │  Gin   │  │  │  │Controller│  │  │ │ HTTP │ │ │\n│  │  │(controller│  │  │  │Server  │  │  │  │ + API    │  │  │ │Server│ │ │\n│  │  │-runtime) │  │  │  │        │  │  │  │ Server   │  │  │ │      │ │ │\n│  │  └────┬───┘  │  │  └───┬────┘  │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │ └──┬───┘ │ │\n│  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │    │     │ │\n│  │  K8s API    │  │  Redis/Store │  │  K8s API      │  │ Workspace │ │\n│  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │    │     │ │\n│  └───────┼──────┘  └──────┼───────┘  └───────┼──────┘  └────┼─────┘ │\n│          │                │                  │              │       │\n│          └────────────────┴──────────────────┴──────────────┘       │\n│                              │                                       │\n│                    Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n│                         + Redis/Valkey                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Binary Responsibilities\n\n#### agentd\n- Parse Kubernetes configuration flags\n- Initialize controller-runtime Manager with Sandbox scheme\n- Start idle cleanup reconciler\n- Handle graceful shutdown on signals\n\n#### router\n- Parse HTTP port and Redis connection flags\n- Initialize Gin HTTP server\n- Wire session routing middleware\n- Connect to workload manager backend\n- Handle graceful HTTP server shutdown\n\n#### workload-manager\n- Parse Kubernetes and Redis configuration\n- Initialize Sandbox controller (reconciler)\n- Start HTTP API server for sandbox management\n- Handle CRD lifecycle operations\n- Coordinate with optional Volcano scheduler\n\n#### picod\n- Parse HTTP port and workspace root flags\n- Initialize workspace directory\n- Start code execution HTTP handlers\n- Provide file upload/download endpoints\n- Support exec streaming for interactive sessions\n\n---\n\n## Execution Flows\n\n### Common Binary Startup Flow\n\n```\nmain()\n    │\n    ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Parse Flags   │\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Validate      │\n│ Required Flags│\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ├─ Missing ──► Print Error + Exit(1)\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Log Startup   │\n│ (version, cfg)│\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Initialize    │\n│ Dependencies  │\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Start Service │\n│ (blocking)    │\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Wait for      │\n│ SIGINT/SIGTERM│\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────┐\n│ Graceful      │\n│ Shutdown      │\n└───────┬───────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n    Exit(0)\n```\n\n### agentd Startup Flow\n\n```\nmain()\n    │\n    ▼\nParse flags: --kubeconfig, --sync-period\n    │\n    ▼\nctrl.GetConfigOrDie() // K8s config\n    │\n    ▼\nscheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    │\n    ▼\nAdd Sandbox v1alpha1 to scheme\n    │\n    ▼\nctrl.NewManager(ctrl.Options{\n    Scheme: scheme,\n    SyncPeriod: syncPeriod,\n})\n    │\n    ▼\nagentd.NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient())\n    │\n    ▼\nSetupWithManager(mgr)\n    │\n    ▼\nmgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n```\n\n### router Startup Flow\n\n```\nmain()\n    │\n    ▼\nParse flags: --port, --redis-addr, --workload-manager\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate required flags\n    │\n    ▼\nredis.NewClient(redisAddr)\n    │\n    ▼\nstore := router.NewSessionStore(redis)\n    │\n    ▼\ngin.New()\n    │\n    ▼\nrouter.SetupRoutes(engine, store, workloadMgrURL)\n    │\n    ▼\nhttp.ListenAndServe()\n    │\n    ▼\nSignal handling for graceful shutdown\n```\n\n### workload-manager Startup Flow\n\n```\nmain()\n    │\n    ▼\nParse flags: --port, --kubeconfig, --redis-addr, --default-image\n    │\n    ▼\nctrl.GetConfigOrDie()\n    │\n    ▼\nscheme := runtime.NewScheme()\nAdd AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter to scheme\n    │\n    ▼\nctrl.NewManager(...)\n    │\n    ▼\nworkloadmanager.NewController(mgr, redis, config)\n    │\n    ▼\nSetup HTTP API server on --port\n    │\n    ▼\nStart both controller and HTTP server\n```\n\n### picod Startup Flow\n\n```\nmain()\n    │\n    ▼\nParse flags: --port, --workspace\n    │\n    ▼\nResolve workspace to absolute path\nCreate if not exists\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate workspace is writable\n    │\n    ▼\nhttp.NewServeMux()\n    │\n    ▼\nRegister handlers:\n  - /execute (code execution)\n  - /upload (file upload)\n  - /download (file download)\n  - /exec (interactive exec)\n    │\n    ▼\nhttp.ListenAndServe()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### agentd Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig (empty = in-cluster) |\n| `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | Full sync period for all sandboxes |\n| `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n| `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n\n### router Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `--debug` | bool | false | Enable debug logging |\n| `--redis-addr` | string | (required) | Redis/Valkey server address |\n| `--workload-manager` | string | (required) | Workload manager URL |\n| `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n| `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n\n### workload-manager Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP API server port |\n| `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig (empty = in-cluster) |\n| `--redis-addr` | string | (required) | Redis/Valkey server address |\n| `--default-image` | string | \"ubuntu:22.04\" | Default sandbox image |\n| `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default namespace |\n| `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n| `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n\n### picod Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `--workspace` | string | \".\" | Workspace root directory |\n| `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | HTTP read header timeout |\n| `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Description | Binary |\n|-------|-------------|--------|\n| `FlagError` | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n| `ConfigError` | Kubernetes config loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n| `ConnectionError` | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n| `SchemeError` | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n| `ServerError` | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n| `WorkspaceError` | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n\n### Exit Codes\n\n| Exit Code | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| 0 | Clean shutdown |\n| 1 | Configuration error |\n| 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n| 3 | Server startup error |\n| 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n| 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\n#### agentd\n| Resource | Verbs |\n|----------|-------|\n| `sandboxes` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n\n#### router\n| Resource | Verbs |\n|----------|-------|\n| `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n\n#### workload-manager\n| Resource | Verbs |\n|----------|-------|\n| `agentruntimes` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n| `codeinterpreters` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `pods` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n| `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n\n#### picod\n- Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n- Workspace directory isolation\n- No Kubernetes API access required\n\n### Sensitive Data\n- Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n- Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n- No secrets logged at startup\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | ~80 | Idle cleanup controller entry point |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | ~100 | Session routing proxy entry point |\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | ~120 | Sandbox orchestration entry point |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | ~90 | Sandbox daemon entry point |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"flag\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"os/signal\"\n    \"syscall\"\n    \"time\"\n    \"context\"\n    \n    // Kubernetes\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n    \n    // HTTP\n    \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n    \n    // Storage\n    \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n    \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n    \n    // AgentCube internal\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Kubernetes controller framework |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | K8s config loading |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for router |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Helm Charts | Deploy binaries as container images |\n| Dockerfiles | Build container images for each binary |\n| CI/CD | Build and test binaries |\n| Local Development | Run services locally with `go run` |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n|--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n| agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n| router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n| workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n| picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Binary with Subcommands\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Simpler deployment; single artifact; shared code |\n| **Cons** | Larger binary size; violates microservices pattern; harder to scale independently; all components must be updated together |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — AgentCube follows microservices architecture; independent scaling and deployment are requirements |\n\n### Alternative 2: Configuration Files Instead of Flags\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | More configuration options; easier to manage complex configs; version controlled |\n| **Cons** | Additional file management; less explicit; harder to debug; requires config reloading logic |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Flags are simpler for containerized environments (12-factor app); config files can be added later if needed |\n\n### Alternative 3: Environment Variables Only\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Cloud-native; works well with Kubernetes secrets; no command-line exposure |\n| **Cons** | Less discoverable; no built-in help; harder to validate at startup |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Flags provide better UX and discoverability; env vars can supplement flags for secrets |\n\n### Alternative 4: Sidecar Pattern for picod\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Separation of concerns; independent updates |\n| **Cons** | More complex deployment; networking overhead; requires shared filesystem |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — picod is designed to run inside sandbox pods as the main process; sidecar adds unnecessary complexity |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Flag parsing inconsistencies across binaries | Medium | Low | Use shared flag helper functions; consistent naming conventions |\n| Missing required flags in production | Medium | High | Fail fast with clear error messages; validate all required flags before startup |\n| Graceful shutdown timeout too short | Low | Medium | Configurable timeout with sensible default (30s); log warnings on timeout |\n| Kubernetes config loading failures | Medium | High | Support both in-cluster and external configs; clear error messages |\n| Redis connection failures at startup | Medium | High | Retry with exponential backoff; fail fast after retries |\n| Binary size bloat from dependencies | Low | Medium | Use build flags `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`; multi-stage Docker builds |\n| Signal handling race conditions | Low | Medium | Use context-based shutdown; proper goroutine synchronization |\n| Port conflicts | Low | Medium | Configurable ports; check port availability; clear error messages |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Build Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build all binaries\ngo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\ngo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\ngo build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\ngo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n\n# Verify binaries exist\nls -la bin/\n```\n\n### Help Verification\n\n```bash\n# Each binary should print help\n./bin/agentd --help\n./bin/router --help\n./bin/workload-manager --help\n./bin/picod --help\n```\n\n### Startup Verification (Local)\n\n```bash\n# Test picod (no external deps)\n./bin/picod --port=18080 &\nsleep 1\ncurl http://localhost:18080/health || echo \"Health check not implemented yet\"\nkill %1\n\n# Test agentd (requires K8s config, will fail gracefully)\n./bin/agentd --kubeconfig=/dev/null 2>&1 | head -5\n\n# Test with missing required flags\n./bin/router 2>&1 | grep -q \"required\" && echo \"Flag validation works\"\n```\n\n### Graceful Shutdown Test\n\n```bash\n# Test graceful shutdown\ntimeout 2 ./bin/picod --port=18081 &\nsleep 0.5\nkill -TERM %1\nwait %1\necho \"Exit code: $?\"  # Should be 0\n```\n\n### Docker Build Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build container images\nmake docker-build\n\n# Verify images\ndocker images | grep agentcube\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-019 Delta Spec](changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md) — Detailed requirements\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n- [Deployment Design](deployment/design.md) — Helm charts and Dockerfiles\n- [CLI Toolkit Design](cli-toolkit/design.md) — Python CLI design\n- [project.md](project.md) — Project context and architecture\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ All 4 binaries compile without errors\n2. ✅ Each binary prints help with `--help` flag\n3. ✅ Each binary validates required flags and exits with error if missing\n4. ✅ agentd starts controller-runtime manager with Sandbox reconciler\n5. ✅ router starts Gin HTTP server and connects to Redis\n6. ✅ workload-manager starts controller and HTTP API server\n7. ✅ picod starts HTTP server and initializes workspace\n8. ✅ All binaries handle SIGINT/SIGTERM for graceful shutdown\n9. ✅ Exit codes are correct (0 for success, non-zero for errors)\n10. ✅ Docker builds succeed for all binaries\n11. ✅ Binaries log startup messages with version and configuration\n\n---\n\n*AR-019 — Module: cmd — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775882114004,"end":1775882114144}}}}
